</opentopic:map><topic break-before="true" is-chapter="true" class="- topic/topic " id="unique_1" topicrefclass="- map/topicref " nd:nd-id="starting_clock" oid="starting_clock" specializations="@props/deliveryTarget">
    <title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph topic/title-wrapper ">Starting Clock</ph></title>
    <body class="- topic/body ">
        <p class="- topic/p ">Windows has its own in built app "Clock" for setting alarms. </p>
        <p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">To start Clock:</b></p>
        <ol class="- topic/ol " id="unique_1_Connect_42_ol_z1h_rf3_bvb" nd:nd-id="ol_z1h_rf3_bvb">
            <li class="- topic/li ">Click the Start Menu.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Hit the Search button and type "Clock".</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Open the Clock Application.</li>
        </ol>
    </body>
<topic class="- topic/topic " id="unique_2" topicrefclass="- map/topicref " nd:nd-id="signing_in" oid="signing_in" specializations="@props/deliveryTarget">
    <title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph topic/title-wrapper ">Signing In</ph></title>
    <body class="- topic/body ">
        <p class="- topic/p ">You can also choose to sign in with your work/personal mail ID in order to sync your
            alarms with your work schedule.</p>
        <ol class="- topic/ol " id="unique_2_Connect_42_ol_a5k_mg3_bvb" nd:nd-id="ol_a5k_mg3_bvb">
            <li class="- topic/li ">Click on the Sign in <image class="- topic/image " height="25" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/sign%20in.png" id="unique_2_Connect_42_image_ivf_c2p_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_ivf_c2p_bvb" placement="inline" width="25">
                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Sign in Image</alt>
                </image> icon on the left navigation bar.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Sign in using your Microsoft Work/School account.</li>
        </ol>
    </body>
</topic></topic><topic break-before="true" is-chapter="true" class="- topic/topic " id="unique_3" topicrefclass="- map/topicref " nd:nd-id="features_of_clock" oid="features_of_clock" specializations="@props/deliveryTarget">
    <title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph topic/title-wrapper ">Features of Clock</ph></title>
    <body class="- topic/body ">
        <p class="- topic/p "/>
    </body>
<topic class="- topic/topic " id="unique_4" topicrefclass="- map/topicref " nd:nd-id="focus_sessions" oid="focus_sessions" specializations="@props/deliveryTarget">
    <title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph topic/title-wrapper ">Focus Sessions</ph></title>
    <body class="- topic/body ">
        <p class="- topic/p ">Focus Sessions allow the user to set a specific time duration for  work periods with
            timely break periods in between, thus improving productivity at work. </p>
    </body>
<topic class="- topic/topic " id="unique_5" topicrefclass="- map/topicref " nd:nd-id="ready_set_focus" oid="ready_set_focus" specializations="@props/deliveryTarget">
    <title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph topic/title-wrapper ">Ready, Set, Focus !</ph></title>
    <body class="- topic/body ">
        <p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">To enable Focus Sessions:</b></p>
        <ol class="- topic/ol " id="unique_5_Connect_42_ol_vtt_wh3_bvb" nd:nd-id="ol_vtt_wh3_bvb">
            <li class="- topic/li ">Click on the Focus Sessions <image class="- topic/image " height="25" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/Focus%20sessions.png" id="unique_5_Connect_42_image_o2c_j2p_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_o2c_j2p_bvb" placement="inline" width="25">
                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Focus sessions image</alt>
                </image> icon on the left navigation toolbar</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Click "Get Started".</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Under the<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> "Ready, Set, Focus"</b> section, Enter the number of minutes you have
                at your disposal.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">If you do not want breaks, tick the checkbox next to "Skip Breaks".</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Click on "Start Focus Section".</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Your focus session begins. </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">The countdown time is tracked and at the end of it, you will receive a reminder
                asking you to take a 5 minute break from work.</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Customize break period and focus period:</b></p>
        <ol class="- topic/ol " id="unique_5_Connect_42_ol_ivt_vj3_bvb" nd:nd-id="ol_ivt_vj3_bvb">
            <li class="- topic/li ">Click the "See More" <image class="- topic/image " height="25" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/See%20more.png" id="unique_5_Connect_42_image_syf_42p_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_syf_42p_bvb" placement="inline" width="25">
                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">See more icon</alt>
                </image> icon in the same section.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Click "View Settings".</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Click on "Focus Periods". </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Select the desired duration of Focus and break periods.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">The changes made in this setting will be reflected when you return to the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">"Ready,
                    Set, Focus"</b> section.</li>
        </ol>
    </body>
</topic><topic class="- topic/topic " id="unique_6" topicrefclass="- map/topicref " nd:nd-id="daily_progress" oid="daily_progress" specializations="@props/deliveryTarget">
    <title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph topic/title-wrapper ">Daily Progress</ph></title>
    <body class="- topic/body ">
        <p class="- topic/p ">This section lets you know how much of your goal has been achieved.</p>
        <p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">To edit your daily goals:</b><ol class="- topic/ol " id="unique_6_Connect_42_ol_b1y_f43_bvb" nd:nd-id="ol_b1y_f43_bvb">
                <li class="- topic/li ">Click the edit <image class="- topic/image " height="25" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/edit.png" id="unique_6_Connect_42_image_l53_xfp_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_l53_xfp_bvb" placement="inline" width="25">
                        <alt class="- topic/alt ">Edit goal</alt>
                    </image> icon in the "Daily Progress" Section.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li ">Set your daily goal duration.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li ">Set the time of the day at which you want to clear records of daily progress and
                    completed tasks everyday.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li ">Tick the checkbox next to "Include weekends in streaks" if you want to include
                    weekends as well.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li ">Click Save.</li>
            </ol></p>
    </body>
</topic><topic class="- topic/topic " id="unique_7" topicrefclass="- map/topicref " nd:nd-id="tasks" oid="tasks" specializations="@props/deliveryTarget">
    <title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph topic/title-wrapper ">Tasks</ph></title>
    <body class="- topic/body ">
        <p class="- topic/p ">This section allows you to add tasks and assign them to your focus sessions throughout
            the day.</p>
        <p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">To add a task:</b><ol class="- topic/ol " id="unique_7_Connect_42_ol_uth_gq3_bvb" nd:nd-id="ol_uth_gq3_bvb">
                <li class="- topic/li ">Click the Add <image class="- topic/image " height="25" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/plus.png" id="unique_7_Connect_42_image_g1z_kgp_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_g1z_kgp_bvb" placement="inline" width="25">
                        <alt class="- topic/alt ">Add button</alt>
                    </image> button in the "Tasks" Section.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li ">Enter the task title and hit the enter button.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li ">Your task is saved.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li ">You can save upto a couple of tasks and select/deselect them for your
                    session.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li ">Click the See more <image class="- topic/image " height="20" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/See%20more.png" id="unique_7_Connect_42_image_mzt_ngp_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_mzt_ngp_bvb" placement="inline" width="20">
                        <alt class="- topic/alt ">See more</alt>
                    </image>icon in order to :<ul class="- topic/ul " id="unique_7_Connect_42_ul_phv_wlj_bvb" nd:nd-id="ul_phv_wlj_bvb">
                        <li class="- topic/li "> Expand task list.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Collapse task list.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Choose a task list. <p class="- topic/p ">From the existing task lists.</p></li>
                    </ul></li>
            </ol></p>
    </body>
</topic><topic class="- topic/topic " id="unique_8" topicrefclass="- map/topicref " nd:nd-id="spotify" oid="spotify" specializations="@props/deliveryTarget">
    <title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph topic/title-wrapper ">Spotify</ph></title>
    <body class="- topic/body ">
        <p class="- topic/p ">Spotify is a digital music, podcast, and video service that gives you access to millions
            of songs and other content from creators all over the world.</p>
        <p class="- topic/p ">You can use the Spotify app to enhance your focus sessions with music and podcasts. </p>
        <p class="- topic/p ">Click on the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Install Spotify</b> Button if you wish to do so.</p>
        <p class="- topic/p ">Click the See more <image class="- topic/image " height="20" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/See%20more.png" id="unique_8_Connect_42_image_urk_sgp_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_urk_sgp_bvb" placement="inline" width="20">
                <alt class="- topic/alt ">See more</alt>
            </image> icon in order to :<ul class="- topic/ul " id="unique_8_Connect_42_ul_ls5_nmj_bvb" nd:nd-id="ul_ls5_nmj_bvb">
                <li class="- topic/li ">Hide Spotify</li>
                <li class="- topic/li ">View/Change Settings for Spotify</li>
            </ul></p>
    </body>
</topic></topic><topic class="- topic/topic " id="unique_9" topicrefclass="- map/topicref " nd:nd-id="timer" oid="timer" specializations="@props/deliveryTarget">
    <title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph topic/title-wrapper ">Timer</ph></title>
    <body class="- topic/body ">
        <p class="- topic/p ">A timer is a specialized type of clock used for measuring specific time intervals. </p>
        <bodydiv class="- topic/bodydiv "/>
        <p class="- topic/p ">Click on the  <image class="- topic/image " height="20" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/timer.png" id="unique_9_Connect_42_image_uhw_vgp_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_uhw_vgp_bvb" placement="inline" width="20">
                <alt class="- topic/alt ">Timer</alt>
            </image> icon on the left navigation toolbar to open the Timer section.</p>
        <p class="- topic/p ">1 minute, 3 minute, 5 minute, 10 minute timers would be present by default. These Timers
            can be started, reset and edited to customize user needs.</p>
        <ul class="- topic/ul " id="unique_9_Connect_42_ul_ybf_4pj_bvb" nd:nd-id="ul_ybf_4pj_bvb">
            <li class="- topic/li ">Click the play icon <image class="- topic/image " height="20" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/play.png" id="unique_9_Connect_42_image_j1b_rpj_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_j1b_rpj_bvb" placement="inline" width="20">
                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Play icon</alt>
                </image>to start the timer of your choice.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Click the Reset icon <image class="- topic/image " height="20" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/reset.png" id="unique_9_Connect_42_image_vqf_vpj_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_vqf_vpj_bvb" placement="inline" width="20">
                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Reset icon</alt>
                </image>to reset the timer.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Click the Expand icon <image class="- topic/image " height="20" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/expand.png" id="unique_9_Connect_42_image_g5j_gqj_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_g5j_gqj_bvb" placement="inline" width="20">
                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">expand icon</alt>
                </image> to expand the timer view. </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Click the Restore icon <image class="- topic/image " height="20" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/restore.png" id="unique_9_Connect_42_image_o25_hqj_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_o25_hqj_bvb" placement="inline" width="20">
                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Restore icon</alt>
                </image> to minimize the expanded view.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Click the Keep on Top <image class="- topic/image " height="20" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/Keep%20on%20top.png" id="unique_9_Connect_42_image_l4d_jqj_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_l4d_jqj_bvb" placement="inline" width="20">
                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Keep on top icon</alt>
                </image>icon to pin the timer to the top of the screen.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">In order to edit any of the timers, right click your mouse button over the timer,
                select "Edit" <image class="- topic/image " height="20" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/edit.png" id="unique_9_Connect_42_image_esp_3rj_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_esp_3rj_bvb" placement="inline" width="20">
                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">edit icon</alt>
                </image> and edit it as required.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">In order to delete a timer,  right click your mouse button over the timer, select
                "Delete" <image class="- topic/image " height="20" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/delete.png" id="unique_9_Connect_42_image_x51_krj_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_x51_krj_bvb" placement="inline" width="20">
                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">delete</alt>
                </image>. </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">In order to add a new timer, click the "Add timer" icon <image class="- topic/image " height="20" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/plus.png" id="unique_9_Connect_42_image_vjh_lrj_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_vjh_lrj_bvb" placement="inline" width="20">
                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Add icon</alt>
                </image> on the bottom right of the window.</li>
        </ul>
    </body>
</topic><topic class="- topic/topic " id="unique_10" topicrefclass="- map/topicref " nd:nd-id="alarm" oid="alarm" specializations="@props/deliveryTarget">
    <title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph topic/title-wrapper ">Alarm</ph></title>
    <body class="- topic/body ">
        <p class="- topic/p ">Using Clock, you can set an alarm to remind you of important tasks throughout the
            week.</p>
        <p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">To set an alarm:</b><ul class="- topic/ul " id="unique_10_Connect_42_ul_ax1_4wn_bvb" nd:nd-id="ul_ax1_4wn_bvb">
                <li class="- topic/li ">Click on the Alarm icon <image class="- topic/image " height="20" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/alarms.png" id="unique_10_Connect_42_image_njf_twn_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_njf_twn_bvb" placement="inline" width="20">
                        <alt class="- topic/alt ">Alarm icon</alt>
                    </image> on the left navigation toolbar.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li ">Click the Add button <image class="- topic/image " height="20" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/plus.png" id="unique_10_Connect_42_image_jbn_vwn_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_jbn_vwn_bvb" placement="inline" width="20">
                        <alt class="- topic/alt ">Add button</alt>
                    </image> to add a new alarm.<p class="- topic/p "><image class="- topic/image " height="400" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/Set%20an%20alarm.png" id="unique_10_Connect_42_image_itf_hhp_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_itf_hhp_bvb" placement="inline" width="200">
                            <alt class="- topic/alt ">Set alarm</alt>
                        </image></p></li>
            </ul></p>
        <ul class="- topic/ul " id="unique_10_Connect_42_ul_vbz_3yn_bvb" nd:nd-id="ul_vbz_3yn_bvb">
            <li class="- topic/li ">Set the alarm time.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Enter a name for the alarm.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Tick the checkbox next to "Repeat Alarm", if you wish to Repeat the alarm on the
                specified day and time in the upcoming weeks.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Select the days of the week on which you want the alarm to ring.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Select your choice of alarm ringtone from the dropdown list.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Select the alarm snooze time from the dropdown.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Click the Save button to save the alarm. </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">To edit alarms:</b></p>
        <ul class="- topic/ul " id="unique_10_Connect_42_ul_fcc_nd4_bvb" nd:nd-id="ul_fcc_nd4_bvb">
            <li class="- topic/li ">Click on the Edit icon <image class="- topic/image " height="20" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/edit.png" id="unique_10_Connect_42_image_pp4_4d4_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_pp4_4d4_bvb" placement="inline" width="20">
                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Edit alarm</alt>
                </image> to edit alarms.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Click on the alarm you wish to edit and make changes.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">To delete alarms:</b></p>
        <ul class="- topic/ul " id="unique_10_Connect_42_ul_y3f_rd4_bvb" nd:nd-id="ul_y3f_rd4_bvb">
            <li class="- topic/li ">Hover the mouse over the alarm card to be deleted and right click.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Click on "Delete" <image class="- topic/image " height="20" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/delete.png" id="unique_10_Connect_42_image_fhl_xd4_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_fhl_xd4_bvb" placement="inline" width="20">
                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Delete alarm</alt>
                </image>.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Alternatively, you can click the Edit icon <image class="- topic/image " height="20" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/edit.png" id="unique_10_Connect_42_image_bds_b24_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_bds_b24_bvb" placement="inline" width="20">
                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Edit</alt>
                </image>on the bottom right end of the window, and then click the Delete icon <image class="- topic/image " height="20" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/delete.png" id="unique_10_Connect_42_image_zy5_c24_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_zy5_c24_bvb" placement="inline" width="20">
                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Delete</alt>
                </image>over the alarm to be deleted.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Click the Done icon <image class="- topic/image " height="20" href="file:/C:/Users/000JB6744/Desktop/Technical%20Writing/Clock/images/done.png" id="unique_10_Connect_42_image_pqm_t24_bvb" nd:nd-id="image_pqm_t24_bvb" placement="inline" width="20">
                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Done icon</alt>
                </image> once deleted.</li>
